<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-69-0407 </DOCNO><TEXT>Three patients with abnormality of corpus callosum diagnosed with MRIwere presented. MRI could reveal the existence of radial distributionand anterior comissure which could not been detected by CT scan. Thesefindings well depicted on sagittal images and accurate diagnosis couldbe obtained. In conclusion, MRI is the best procedure for the diagnosisin malformations of corpus callosum.</TEXT></DOC>